Former Nigerian forward, Nwankwo Kanu has reiterated that the Super Eagles are in a good position to lift the 2021 Africa Cup of Nations in Cameroon. Kanu stated this after Nigeria won all their group stage matches to qualify to the knockout stages of the tournament. The Super Eagles defeated Egypt 1-0, Sudan 3-1 before overcoming Guinea-Bissau 2-0 on Wednesday.   People beginning to respect Super Eagles, says Coach…     Iheanacho cried hard when he was dropped for last AFCON…     AFCON round of 16: Akanni urges Eguavoen to maintain opening…   Reacting, the Atlanta Olympic gold medalist, tweeted: “KAN U believe it? The #afcon group stage is over. Nigeria with the clean sheet. - Advertisement - “Well done Super Eagles. Thank you everyone for supporting them. We are bringing this cup home, Trophy Believe.”